ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Any cattle person who has experienced _M.bovis_ will likely find it easier to believe the disease has been there for some time, as the disease is virtually impossible to eliminate.

As any regulator will tell you, pouring enough money, energy, and time into a disease will have an impact on the disease.

The ones caught in the middle of these 2 somewhat divergent points of view are the folks who own the cattle, as well as the taxpayers who are paying for the testing and slaughtering of affected animals. The animal owner is likely not getting anywhere near what was invested in the animal or what he should make, which puts the animal owner between the proverbial rock and hard place for keeping his operation afloat, so to speak.

Determining when the disease entered the country, if it is really possible to make such a determination, may lend evidence to continue or discontinue the current eradication efforts. - Mod.TG

